The paper discusses wireless visual sensor networks and their energy consumption, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the processing of video frames and the use of multimedia subsystems, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) as possible sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a balanced cluster-tree topology, which is a common approach in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper derives analytic results, which suggests information theory (cs.IT) as a possible sub-category.
